{{Other uses|Accident on the Rampe de Laffrey (disambiguation){{!}}Accident on the Rampe de Laffrey}}
[[Image:Rampe de Laffrey Accident du 18-juillet-1975.jpg|thumb|right|175px|Memorial to the pilgrims killed in the accident]]

The '''accident on the Rampe de Laffrey''' on July 18, 1973, remains, {{As of|2017|lc=on}}, the worst to ever have occurred along [[Rampe de Laffrey|that stretch of roadway]], among the worst in [[France]].<ref name=chretien>[http://www.journalchretien.net/spip.php?article13675 Le Journal Chretien<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  A [[bus]] was carrying [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[pilgrim]]s from [[Braine-le-Comte]] returning from a visit to the shrine of [[Our Lady of La Salette]]; it missed a [[curve]] at the base of the road, near its intersection with the bridge over the [[Romanche]], and overturned.  Forty-three people were killed and six injured in the resulting crash.<ref name=chretien/><ref>Some references give other numbers of injured; all agree on the number of dead.</ref>  After the crash the [[mayor]] of [[Laffrey]] condemned the route as being particularly dangerous, as it had already claimed over one hundred lives over the previous quarter-century.<ref name="Dauphine1">''Le Dauphiné Libéré'', July 23, 1973</ref>

The accident is sometimes referred to as the '''accident de Vizille''' because it occurred very close to the entrance of the town of [[Vizille|that name]]; the crash site, however, is actually located within the boundaries of the [[communes of France|commune]] of [[Notre-Dame-de-Mésage]].  Today a memorial to the victims stands at the site of the accident; it claims the number of dead as forty-five.<ref>http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/25/Rampe_de_Laffrey_Accident_du_18-juillet-1975.jpg</ref>

