[[image:Festival of Lights, New Plymouth, New Zealand.jpg|thumb|Pukekura Park, New Plymouth, New Zealand, illuminated during the annual Festival of Lights.]] [[image:Trees at the Festival of Lights.jpg|thumb|Pukekura Park, New Plymouth, New Zealand, illuminated during the annual Festival of Lights.]] [[image:FestivalofLights-waterfall-lowerstages.jpg|thumb|right|Waterfall lights]] The '''TSB Festival of Lights''' is an annual event held in [[Pukekura Park]], [[New Plymouth]]. Running for free every year from mid-December to early February, it has daytime and night time programmes of events for people of all ages, and the festival itself transforms the park into an illuminated wonderland every evening.
Colourful lights are used to highlight tree crowns, ferns, and other plants. Light art displays are installed along the festival walking route and the waterfall is lit in changing colors. [[image:Waterfall at the Festival of Lights.jpg|thumb|Pukekura Park, New Plymouth, New Zealand, illuminated during the annual Festival of Lights.]] The festival has been a major summer attraction and cultural event for the city since 1993,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nz2011.govt.nz/realnzfestival/events/131-taranaki-festival-of-lights |title=Taranaki Festival of Lights |publisher=NewZealand2011 |accessdate=4 February 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101114193140/http://www.nz2011.govt.nz/realnzfestival/events/131-taranaki-festival-of-lights |archivedate=14 November 2010 |df= }}</ref> and is attended by over 100,000 people each year.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/taranaki-daily-news/news/4601980/Festival-of-Lights-attracts-community-visitors|title=Festival of Lights attracts community, visitors|first=Kate |last=Saunders |date=1 February 2011 |accessdate=4 February 2011|publisher=Taranaki Daily News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/taranaki-daily-news/news/76461466/new-plymouths-festival-of-lights-wraps-up-another-successful-year.html| title=New Plymouth's Festival of Lights wraps up another successful year| first=Tara| last=Shaskey| publisher=Taranaki Daily News| date=1 February 2016}}</ref> The festival celebrated its 20th year in 2013.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.festivaloflights.nz| title=TSB Bank Festival of Lights| publisher=NPDC}}</ref>
==Sponsorship== The festival is sponsored by [[TSB (New Zealand)|TSB Bank]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nzonline.org.nz/festivaloflights.htm |title=TSB Bank Festival of Lights |publisher=nzonline.org.nz}}</ref>
