The '''Frog Fire''' was a fatal fire that occurred during the [[2015 California wildfires|2015 California wildfire season]] that burned {{convert|4,863|acre|ha|0|abbr=on}} of land in the [[Modoc National Forest]].<ref name=inci/> The fire was one of many fires that was started on July 30 during a [[lightning]] storm.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mad River Complex Fire|url=http://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/4436/|website=[[InciWeb]]|accessdate=30 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Humboldt Lightning Fires|url=http://cdfdata.fire.ca.gov/incidents/incidents_details_info?incident_id=1170|website=[[CAL FIRE]]|accessdate=27 August 2015}}</ref>

==Fatality==
On July 31, a [[United States Forest Service]] member from [[South Dakota]] died of [[carbon monoxide poisoning]] while battling the fire.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Locke|first1=Cathy|title=Firefighter at Frog fire died of carbon monoxide poisoning, smoke inhalation, autopsy shows|url=http://www.sacbee.com/news/local/crime/article29989782.html|accessdate=28 August 2015|agency=[[Sacramento Bee]]|date=4 August 2015}}</ref> David Ruhl, a captain with South Dakota's [[Black Hills National Forest]], had vanished the night before.<ref name=cbs>{{cite news|title=Wildfires kill firefighter, force hundreds to flee homes|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/california-wildfires-kill-firefighter-hundreds-flee-homes/|accessdate=31 August 2015|agency=[[CBS News]]|date=1 August 2015}}</ref>

