'''James Gerard Richard Shortt''' (born 16 September 1953) is the [[Director General]] of the International Bodyguard Association (IBA)<ref name="ibabodyguards.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibabodyguards.com/cms/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=33&Itemid=69&lang=en|title=International Bodyguard Association - History|accessdate=6 February 2009|website=ibabodyguards.com|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120731100059/http://www.ibabodyguards.com/cms/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=33&Itemid=69&lang=en|archivedate=31 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> and author of several books on military special forces and martial arts.

On several occasions Shortt has been exposed by British [[tabloid newspapers]] for [[Military imposter|passing himself off]] as a much-decorated [[Special Air Service|SAS]] and [[Parachute Regiment (United Kingdom)|Parachute Regiment]] veteran, as well as exposing his claims to other military and nobiliary credentials.<ref name="thesun.co.uk-1"/><ref name="thesun.co.uk-2"/>

==Career==
Shortt has been the Director-General of the International Bodyguard Association since February 1990.<ref name="IBADeutch">{{cite web|title=I.B.A. Deutschland - International Bodyguard Association|url=http://www.iba-deutschland.de/german/j_shortt.php|website=www.iba-deutschland.de|accessdate=25 June 2016}}</ref> Shortt has also authored several books dealing with military special forces units-particularly the British SAS, as well as been interviewed by other authors on military subjects.

