===Bestgore.com===
[[Bestgore.com|BestGore]] is notorious for its extremely graphic content, such as photos and videos of murders, suicides and violent accidents. It is currently the most visited shock website in the world, with an estimated 15–20 million monthly visits. In July 2013, the website's creator, Slovakian-Canadian Mark Marek, was charged with one count of "corrupting morals", related to his posting of the video of the [[Luka_Magnotta#Murder_of_Lin_Jun|murder of Lin Jun]] on his website.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://globalnews.ca/news/723495/police-charge-edmonton-gore-site-owner-in-magnotta-video-investigation/|title=Edmonton gore site owner charged in Magnotta video investigation released on bail|date=18 July 2013|work=Global News|accessdate=31 October 2014}}</ref> He pleaded guilty and was given a six-month [[Conditional sentence (Canada)|conditional sentence]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Reith|first1=Terry|title=Mark Marek, who posted Magnotta murder video, pleads guilty to corrupting morals|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/edmonton/marek-trial-opens-1.3416408|accessdate=6 April 2016|publisher=CBC/Radio-Canada|date=25 January 2016}}</ref>

===Goatse.cx===
[[Goatse.cx|Goatse]]<ref name="scotsman"/><ref name="The Hands of God"/> was one of the best-known shock sites, featuring an image of a man stretching his [[anus]] with his hands.<ref name="scotsman" /><ref>{{cite news|title=Goatse.cx; Distended?| first=Pawan| last=Kumar|publisher=Yaziyo News|date=2008-11-11}}</ref> The site featured a page devoted to fan-submitted artwork and tributes to the site,<ref name="scotsman"/><ref name="The Hands of God">{{cite web|url=http://www.snopes.com/photos/natural/godhands.asp| title=The Hands of God|date=15 June 2007|publisher=[[Snopes.com]]|accessdate=2009-08-03}}</ref> and a parody of the image was also shown by a [[BBC]] newscast as an alternative for the then recently unveiled logo for the [[2012 Summer Olympics]].<ref name= "shock tactics"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://blogs.guardian.co.uk/technology/archives/2007/06/08/updated_b3ta_hacks_the_bbc_with_olympic_goatse.html|title=B3ta hacks the BBC with Olympic goatse|work=The Guardian|location=[[London]]|first=Robert 'Bobbie'|last=Johnson|date=June 8, 2007|accessdate=May 23, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080619041238/http://blogs.guardian.co.uk/technology/archives/2007/06/08/updated_b3ta_hacks_the_bbc_with_olympic_goatse.html|dead-url=yes|archive-date=19 June 2008}}</ref>

The site was shut down in 2004; however, various [[mirror website|mirror sites]] featuring the image still exist.<ref name ="Russian mirror">{{cite web|title=goatse.ru|url=http://goatse.ru/|accessdate=18 February 2013}}</ref> In 2012, it was resurrected as an e-mail service.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/business/2012/11/how-goatse-cx-went-from-shock-site-to-webmail-service/|title=How goatse.cx went from shock site to webmail service|last=Hutchinson|first=Lee|work=[[Ars Technica]]|date=2012-11-19|accessdate=2014-11-02}}</ref>

=== Meatspin ===
'''Meatspin''' is a shock site containing a looping video of a man and a [[trans woman|transsexual woman]] engaged in sexual activity while the receiving partner's penis spins endlessly. A counter keeps track of how many spins you've watched,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/never-google-these-phrases|title=9 Seemingly Innocent Phrases You Should Never, Ever Google at Work|last=Moore|first=Jack|website=GQ|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-27}}</ref><ref name="Hartley-Parkinson">{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2015/02/04/jimmys-o2-meatspin_n_6612652.html|title=Gay Porn On O2 Restaurant Booking Screen Leaves Diner Feeling Sick|last=Hartley-Parkinson|first=Richard|website=Huffington Post|language=en-UK|access-date=2017-01-27}}</ref> with the supposed male viewer being mocked as [[Homosexuality|gay]] after watching 50 spins.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.meatspin.fr|title=Meatspin|last=|first=|website=Meatspin|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-27}}</ref> In 2013, a student at Florida State University hacked the wireless network of his campus and redirected all traffic to Meatspin.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.miaminewtimes.com/news/fsu-campus-wi-fi-users-redirected-to-meat-spin-shock-site-by-hacker-6528517|title=FSU Campus Wi-Fi Users Redirected to "Meat Spin" Shock Site by Hacker|last=Munzenrieder|first=Kyle|website=Miami New Times|access-date=2016-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gawker.com/5990105/florida-state-student-faces-felony-charges-for-redirecting-schools-wifi-users-to-infamous-shock-site|title=Florida State Student Faces Felony Charges for Redirecting School's Wifi Users to Infamous Shock Site|last=Zimmerman|first=Neetzan|website=Gawker|language=en-US|access-date=2016-04-06}}</ref> In 2015 consternation followed when a family restaurant played the website in front of some young children.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://metro.co.uk/2015/02/03/family-saw-hardcore-gay-porn-playing-on-restaurant-computer-5047875/|title=Family saw hardcore gay porn playing on restaurant computer|last=Hartley-ParkinsonRichard Hartley-Parkinson|first=Richard|website=Metro|language=en-UK|access-date=2017-01-27}}</ref><ref name="Hartley-Parkinson"/> In 2016 the website was played on a public digital billboard in [[Sweden]], resulting in international media attention.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/malmo-porn-billboard-bus-stop-advert-meatspin_uk_57308ea8e4b0ade291a23609|title=Meatspin Porn Website Somehow Ends Up On Bus Stop In Malmö, Sweden|last=Barrell|first=Ryan|website=Huffington Post|language=en-UK|access-date=2017-01-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techworm.net/2016/05/someone-hacked-billboard-malmo-sweden-show-hardcore-porn.html|title= Someone hacked a billboard in Malmo, Sweden to show hardcore porn|last=Prabhu|first=Vijay|website=Techworm|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.expressen.se/kvallsposten/reklamskylt-visade-grov-porr-pa-stationen/|title=Reklamskylt visade grov porr på stationen|last=Samuelson|first=Fredrik|website=Expressen|language=sv|access-date=2017-01-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/billboard-hijacked-porn-sweden/1394111| title=Billboard hijacked with porn in Sweden| last=Oakes|first=Omar|website=Campaign|language=en-UK|access-date=2017-01-27}}</ref>

===Lemonparty===
'''Lemonparty.org''' is a shock site that contains an image of three elderly naked men in a bed kissing and having oral sex. The song "[[If You Wanna Be Happy]]" by [[Jimmy Soul]] formerly played in the background. The image has been mentioned on some television shows, such as in a sketch on ''[[Talkshow with Spike Feresten]]'',<ref>{{cite web | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080309165446/http://www.bestweekever.tv/tag/Lemon+Party |url=http://www.bestweekever.tv/tag/Lemon+Party |title = Lemon party | publisher= Best week ever TV | archivedate= 2008-03-09 | accessdate = 2012-11-18}}</ref> and dialogue on ''[[Archer (2009 TV series)|Archer]]'', ''[[The Simpsons]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0Jftig3yHP8 |title=The Simpsons – Lemonparty.org reference |publisher=YouTube |date=2011-01-17 |accessdate=2012-11-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110307092023/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0Jftig3yHP8 |archivedate=7 March 2011 }}</ref> ''[[The Cleveland Show]]'', ''[[American Dad!]]'' and ''[[30 Rock]]''. ''30 Rock'' made at least three allusions to a "Lemon party", including when [[Liz Lemon]]'s father, [[List of 30 Rock characters#Dick Lemon|Dick Lemon]], says, "It wouldn't be a Lemon party without old Dick!"<ref name = "college">{{cite web | url=http://www.collegehumor.com/video/3133272/liz-lemon-party | title=Liz Lemon Party | publisher=[[CollegeHumor]] | date=December 14, 2007 | quote=It's not a Lemon party without old Dick! | accessdate=November 5, 2012}}</ref><ref name="hf">{{cite web | url= http://www.hitfix.com/whats-alan-watching/season-premiere-review-30-rock-the-beginning-of-the-end-tank-it | title=Season première review: '30 Rock' – 'The Beginning of the End': Tank it! | publisher=[[HitFix]] | date=October 5, 2012 | quote = ...because there's nothing worse than a surprise Lemon party | accessdate = November 5, 2012 | last = Sepinwall | first = Alan}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url =https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v-bvHlb2Fe8 |title=It isn't a Lemon Party without old Dick | publisher= Google | work = YouTube | date= 2009-06-03 |accessdate= 2012-11-18}}</ref> The website has also been described by [[Jimmy Fallon]] on the ''[[Opie and Anthony]]'' radio show,<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J4sA0wc4z0Y | title= Opie & Anthony – Jimmy Fallon Lemon Party | publisher = Google | work = YouTube | date= 2011-07-15 | accessdate = 2012-11-18}}</ref> on [[Chelsea Handler]]'s TV show ''[[Chelsea Lately]]'',<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UaZnDJhI1dw | title = Chelsea Handler talks about Lemonparty.org |publisher= Google | work = YouTube |date=2010-03-19 | accessdate = 2012-11-18}}</ref> [[Michael J. Nelson]] from RiffTrax.com during the [[RiffTrax]] for ''[[Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.rifftrax.com/rifftrax/avatar |title = Avatar |publisher=RiffTrax |date=2010-04-22 |accessdate= 2012-11-18}}</ref> by [[Jon Stewart]] on ''[[The Daily Show]]'', and ''[[American Dad!]]'',<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.tvequals.com/2012/10/07/american-dad-season-8-episode-2-killer-vacation/american-dad-season-8-episode-2-killer-vacation-3/ | title =American Dad Season 8 Episode 2 Killer Vacation (3) #240300 |publisher=TV equals | accessdate = 2012-11-18}}</ref> by [[Michael Cera]] and [[Jonah Hill]] during promotion for the film ''[[Superbad (film)|SuperBad]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Superbad Stars Plug Lemonparty.org|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QspVBPkmP5Q|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=6 April 2015}}</ref>
